<not id="dQkdkFy5+EGu7LxuJ2o8yQ" >
<dsc reserve="290" >isSetted Checks to see if all tanks exept the one with the turn are setted(ie. not in mid air or moving).	If isSetted returns true drawFrame does not bother drawing all the other tanks and the background. It just uses the old version. for demonstartion sake i'll asume that it is not setted</dsc>
</not>
<not id="q/OsvRNcBEmgmpbVJ8UDnQ" >
<dsc reserve="263" >all average (ie. not current) tanks are drawn first onto a bitmap. then this bitmap is drawn onto anouther bitmap which the current tank and its bombs and blasts are drawn onto. this may seam like a weird way of doing it but it save drawing every tank every time.</dsc>
</not>
